# Repository standards

## Semantic versioning

- Application version lives in `Directory.Build.props` as `Version` (SemVer 2.0: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`).
- For releases, also update `CHANGELOG.md` and follow `RELEASING.md`. Git tags use `v` prefix (e.g. `v1.2.3`).

## Commits and change hygiene

- Prefer [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/): `type(scope): summary` with ASCII-only subject lines.
- Keep diffs focused; avoid unrelated refactors in the same change as a feature or fix.
- User-facing behavior changes should include a `CHANGELOG.md` entry under `[Unreleased]` unless purely internal.

## Security

- Never commit secrets (passwords, tokens, private keys, populated `.env`). Scan changes before suggesting commits.
- Document operator-facing security tradeoffs in README or SECURITY when behavior affects remote systems (SSH, Docker).

## Platform and output

- This is a **WPF** app targeting **Windows**; build verification expects `dotnet build` on Windows for full UI compilation.
- Prefer ASCII in operator-facing console or log strings where Windows code pages matter.

## Docs for agents and humans

- Coding agent entry point: `AGENTS.md`.
- Contributor-facing: `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
